==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hafnium
<hw>haf"ni*um</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧f"n⟦emac⟧*⟦ucr⟧m or
h⟦aum⟧f"n⟦emac⟧*⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A metallic element of
atomic number 72 present together with zirconium to the extent of 1% to
5% in zirconium minerals. It is a poisonous, ductile metal with a
brilliant silver luster, has an atomic weight of 178.49, and has a high
melting point (2227⟦deg⟧ C). It is used in nuclear reactors, and
incandescent lamps as a scavenger of oxygen and nitrogen. See also
<er>norium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haft</ent>⟦br⟧
